          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "So averaging the randomly reconstructed data from a training set will result in a smaller reconstruction error with high probability of  $ 1 - \\mathcal{O}(\\exp(-n)) $ when we use a large n.",
